draw((0,0)--(11,1.7));
draw((10,0)--(11,1.7));
[/asy] Finally, $OS$ is the hypotenuse of right triangle $\triangle OTS$ with $OT=TS=8$.  Hence $OS=\sqrt{8^2+8^2}=\boxed{8\sqrt{2}}$.

problem:
The area of trapezoid $ABCD$ is $164 \text{cm}^2$.  The altitude is $8 \text{cm}$, $AB$ is $10 \text{cm}$, and $CD$ is $17 \text{cm}$.  What is $BC$, in centimeters? [asy]
