Note that \begin{align*}
f(0) &= a(0)^2+b(0)+c \\
&=c
\end{align*}and \begin{align*}
f(1) &= a(1)^2+b(1)+c \\
&=a+b+c.
\end{align*}Thus, \begin{align*}
a+b+2c &= c + (a+b+c) \\
&= f(0)+f(1).
\end{align*}The graph of $y=f(x)$ passes through $(0,7)$ and $(1,4)$, so $f(0)=7$ and $f(1)=4$. Therefore, $a+b+2c = 7 + 4 = \boxed{11}$.

